    "faq": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "item_mwqh3i": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "1.What electric dirt bikes does Megawheels Dirt Bike offer?",
            "content": "<p>Megawheels D2 Series offers three electric dirt bike models: the D2 Lite,D2 and D2 Pro.The D2 Lite is an ideal entry-level electric dirt bike, featuring 14\"/12\" wheels, a 3000 W peak mid-drive motor, and a 48V/23.4 Ah battery, delivering a top speed of 37.28 MPH.The D2 is the high-performance upgrade, equipped with a 3550W peak mid-drive motor, 48V/26Ah battery, 14\"/12\"wheels, and a top speed of 38 MPH.The D2 Pro is the flagship model, equipped with a 4800W peak mid-drive motor, 60V/30Ah battery, 17\"/14\" wheels, and a top speed of 50 MPH.All models come with full hydraulic brakes, dual shock absorption, and three speed modes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_H4aL7L": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "2.What is the top speed and range of the Megawheels D2 Pro electric dirt bike?",
            "content": "<p>At its top speed of 80 km/h, the estimated riding time is about 44 minutes, with a range of approximately 29 km.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_kT6Y8w": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "3.Why does Megawheels D2 Series Dirt Bike use a mid-drive motor instead of a hub motor?",
            "content": "<p>A mid-drive motor offers several key advantages over a hub motor:- Better handling with a more balanced center of gravity. - Stronger low-speed torque for climbing and acceleration. - Better heat dissipation for consistent performance. - Easier to push when the battery is out. - Lighter wheels for improved agility and easier maintenance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_cAjBfj": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "4.Which Megawheels electric dirt bike is right for me— D2 or D2 Pro?",
            "content": "<p>The D2 is ideal for beginners, while the D2 Pro is recommended for riders with prior electric dirt bike experience.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_Y9nR8g": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "5.How long does it take to charge a Megawheels D2 Pro electric dirt bike?",
            "content": "<p>7 hours</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_x7nYLL": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "6.Is the Megawheels electric dirt bike street legal?",
            "content": "<p>Subject to local regulations. Riders who meet the applicable legal requirements and documentation can ride on public roads where permitted.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_KgFM3z": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "7. What age is the Megawheeels D2 pro electric dirt bike suitable for?",
            "content": "<p>Suitable for riders aged 13+.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_rdePUz": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "8. What warranty does Megawheels offer on its electric dirt bikes?",
            "content": "<p>Megawheels D2 Series electric dirt bikes supports a 30‑day return and refund policy. For returns due to non‑quality issues, customers are required to pay the round‑trip shipping costs. In addition, it comes with a 1‑year warranty.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_xzB8Wd": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "9. Does Megawheels offer free shipping on electric dirt bikes?",
            "content": "<p>Yes, free shipping is offered on all Megawheels electric dirt bikes.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
